{"key":"post-5400036","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>5400036</id>\n<content>With the moisture required for bulk substrates or casing material, a soil moisture tester will most likely peg out.   We adjust moisture for our substrates by using 'field moisture level' which is achieved when you can pick up a handful of substrate or casing and no water flows out by gravity.  However if you squeeze gently, a few drops will come out, and if you squeeze very hard, a light stream will drip out.  After practicing a few times, you'll get perfect moisture content.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>5400090</next>\n<prev>5399880</prev>\n<first>5399618</first>\n<last>5400090</last>\n<when>1142381171</when>\n<utime>03/15/06 02:06 AM</utime>\n</post>"}